            "content": {
                "type": "steps",
                "items": [
                    "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a kettlebell in one hand.",
                    "Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your abs engaged.",
                    "Let the kettlebell hang straight down from your arm.",
                    "Slowly pull the kettlebell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body.",
                    "Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position.",
                    "Repeat for the desired number of reps, then switch sides and repeat with the other arm."
